            "text": "AI agents work by combining a language model with tools (like file read/write and shell access) inside a loop. The model receives a prompt, decides which tool to call, gets the result, and loops back to decide what to do next. Three tools — read file, write file, and run shell — form a universal basis that lets agents do almost anything a developer can."
